  "title": "Casual Conversations in New Alderaan",
  "summary": "In Organa Park on Ord Mantell's New Alderaan, the closely-guarded former Imperial commodore Lynae Caiton strikes up a frank conversation with the young Republic pilot Gene, who is feeding swans by a fountain; the two compare Imperial and Republic attitudes toward family, military life, and old grudges before Gene leaves for training maneuvers. The scene shifts to Chianar Plaza, where the shopkeeper Rasi feeds birds and reconnects with the swoop racer Shael, spotting Lynae and her escorts touring the art gallery. A brash, cat-suited young woman named Serenella interrupts to demand armor from Rasi's shop and trades barbs with the other women, prompting a cutting lecture from Lynae about the difference between pretty and stupid. The pleasant, prickly exchange winds down as Lynae, now styling herself the retired Doctor Cassius, moves on through the plaza.",
